heading_context: Check a job applicant's right to work: use their share code
chunks.html_content:
Check details of a job applicant’s right to work in the UK, including:

  • the types of work they’re allowed to do
  • how long they can work in the UK for, if there’s a time limit

You’ll need the job applicant’s:

  • date of birth
  • right to work share code

You can also check someone’s original documents instead - for example if you do not have a share code.

heading_context: Check a job applicant's right to work: use their share code
chunks.html_content: British and Irish citizens cannot get a share code. You can check their physical documents yourself or use an online identity service provider (IDSP) to check them.
